The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Lo-Cal

Derek O'Brien

 The name Calcutta seems to pop up in the most unlikely places. Do you know 

there was a Calcutta even in Captain William Bligh?s life? Yes, the same Captain 

Bligh who was involved in the famous mutiny on the Bounty in 1789. In 1795, he 

was the captain of a ship named HMS Calcutta. Incidentally, Captain Bligh?s 

250th birthday was celebrated last year

 QUESTIONS

 Histori-cal 

1. Walter Granville was the architect of which famous building in Calcutta? 

2. Who was the first patron of the Asiatic Society of Calcutta? 3. 

The construction work of the Victoria Memorial was entrusted to which company?

 Aestheti-Cal

4. Which Calcutta-based painter illustrated the Constitution of India? 

5. Who founded the Oriental Art Society in 1907? 6. Bikash Bhattacharjee 

illustrated Samaresh Basu?s biography of which famous sculptor?

 TOPI-CAL

 Zoologi-Cal Raja Rajendro Mullick Bahadur founded the Marble Palace 

Zoo in Chorbagan, Calcutta in 1854. He was a student of natural history and the 

zoo in his house had creatures collected from different parts of the world as 

well as India. 

ANSWERS 

 1. GPO or General Post Office; 2. Warren Hastings; 3. Messrs Martin amp; Co.; 

4. Nandalal Bose; 5. Abanindranath Tagore; 6. Ramkinkar Beij 




